1
00:00:48,510 --> 00:00:52,970
[The Ferry Man: 10th Anniversary]

2
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:56,000
[Episode 2]

3
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:02,850
The magic can only last for one night?

4
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,260
Send it back yourself.

5
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:06,950
Is there any other magic

6
00:01:06,950 --> 00:01:08,280
that lasts a bit longer?

7
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:10,140
I said, send it back yourself.

8
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:12,480
Fine.

9
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,640
We couldn't really communicate anyway;

10
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,240
there's a language barrier.

11
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,480
He's a foreigner?

12
00:01:20,230 --> 00:01:21,310
Does he speak Chinese?

13
00:01:21,310 --> 00:01:22,039
Chinese?

14
00:01:22,539 --> 00:01:23,510
He doesn't even speak English;

15
00:01:23,510 --> 00:01:24,770
he only speaks French.

16
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,870
Good thing I have a translation app.

17
00:01:26,870 --> 00:01:28,200
Well, how was your chat?

18
00:01:28,230 --> 00:01:29,400
Nothing much.

19
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:32,150
He fell in love with me at first sight,

20
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:34,039
recited some love poems or something,

21
00:01:34,039 --> 00:01:35,680
then said he wanted to marry me,

22
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:36,590
have kids,

23
00:01:37,039 --> 00:01:37,640
and even teach me

24
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,900
how to make the bread
his mom used to bake.

25
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,140
There's a generation gap.

26
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:44,330
More like a centuries-long time warp.

27
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:47,120
Two coffees? I only ordered one.

28
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,000
Is the other one on the house?

29
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,460
They're both on the house.

30
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:50,650
The new beans

31
00:01:50,759 --> 00:01:52,420
we got in today are excellent.

32
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:53,289
Give it a try.

33
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:55,000
I don't drink coffee.

34
00:01:55,310 --> 00:01:56,070
Did you forget, uncle?

35
00:01:56,070 --> 00:01:57,350
Not hot; I want it iced.

36
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,420
Did you forget?

37
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,760
Let's practice more by then.

38
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:03,560
Arrange another game with them.

39
00:02:04,050 --> 00:02:05,280
Sir, do you have a restroom?

40
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,270
May we use it?

41
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:07,710
Out in the backyard.

42
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:09,039
-Thanks, sir.
-Thanks.

43
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,490
Let's go.

44
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:11,710
That's not how we should play.

45
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:12,310
Hurry up.

46
00:02:12,330 --> 00:02:13,930
Let's go. Quit wasting time.

47
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,060
That backpack looks so heavy.

48
00:02:24,710 --> 00:02:26,040
I'd say it's over 30 jin.

49
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,810
Kids these days
have a heavy school workload.

50
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,800
I don't see any boy with a backpack.

51
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:46,160
What are you two talking about?

52
00:02:47,710 --> 00:02:48,630
What's there to talk about then?

53
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:51,090
Let's go practice. Let's go.

54
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,520
Nice. It's pretty nice.

55
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:53,560
Right?

56
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:05,400
Ghosts

57
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:06,680
shouldn't be appearing in broad daylight,

58
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:07,280
right?

59
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:08,810
Found it.

60
00:03:11,590 --> 00:03:14,280
It's a looping spirit,
one of the four types of ghosts.

61
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,710
Unlike ordinary ghosts,

62
00:03:15,790 --> 00:03:16,810
they don't know

63
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:17,710
they're dead.

64
00:03:17,940 --> 00:03:19,680
They just repeat the scene from the day

65
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:21,010
they died over and over.

66
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,180
Obsession.

67
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,000
Do you night watchmen

68
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,150
deal with things like this?

69
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:28,560
We do.

70
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:30,490
Of course we do.

71
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:35,570
[Chapter 2: Night Watchmen]

72
00:03:31,430 --> 00:03:32,260
We night watchmen

73
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:33,870
empowered by the righteousness
of heaven and earth,

74
00:03:33,870 --> 00:03:34,730
are dedicated to ridding the world

75
00:03:34,730 --> 00:03:36,990
of treacherous fiends and evil spirits!

76
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:41,160
Where's the music coming from?

77
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:43,370
I'm playing it on my phone.

78
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:45,079
Every time I recite that speech,

79
00:03:45,079 --> 00:03:46,210
this background music

80
00:03:46,210 --> 00:03:48,070
makes it sound more... imposing.

81
00:03:55,970 --> 00:03:58,000
[Class 2, Senior 3]

82
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:26,730
Hello, Granny.

83
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:08,890
You're back.

84
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:10,950
How were your classes today?

85
00:05:10,950 --> 00:05:11,680
Pretty good.

86
00:05:11,830 --> 00:05:12,630
Are you tired?

87
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,850
Go back to your room and review.

88
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:23,190
It's still early.

89
00:05:23,270 --> 00:05:24,120
Only 10 o'clock.

90
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:26,150
Review for another three hours tonight.

91
00:05:26,150 --> 00:05:27,680
Mom will make some chicken soup for you.

92
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,070
Okay.

93
00:05:35,159 --> 00:05:35,920
Dapeng,

94
00:05:36,390 --> 00:05:37,510
you must work hard.

95
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,770
You're repeating the year.

96
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:41,280
Do you know how much

97
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,710
a year's tutoring costs?

98
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:44,190
If you fail again,

99
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:46,070
Mom will be really heartbroken.

100
00:05:46,940 --> 00:05:47,650
Look at

101
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:49,350
[Final Sprint
for the College Entrance Exam]

102
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,120
your third great-uncle's child—

103
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,560
he got into a top-tier university
on his first try.

104
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,630
You're not naturally bright,

105
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:54,430
so you have to work twice as hard!

106
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,600
You can't let Mom

107
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,600
lose face in front of the relatives.

108
00:05:58,950 --> 00:06:00,550
This chicken is really good.

109
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:02,030
Free-range chicken.

110
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:02,850
I picked it up

111
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:04,400
at the market this morning.

112
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:05,710
[Good Luck on the College Entrance Exam]

113
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:06,820
I've pinned

114
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:08,600
all my hopes on you.

115
00:06:09,430 --> 00:06:10,630
As long as you can get into

116
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:11,750
a good university,

117
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:15,490
every hardship and sacrifice I make
will be worth it.

118
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,390
This is it.

119
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:26,600
Actually,

120
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:29,040
we could just clear it with a spell.

121
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:31,240
But looping spirits

122
00:06:31,650 --> 00:06:32,920
only trap themselves in their own memories

123
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:34,040
and don't harm people.

124
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:36,040
If we just eliminate it outright...

125
00:06:36,190 --> 00:06:37,190
It's a bit pitiful

126
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:39,480
if we just reduce it to nothing.

127
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:42,680
After all,

128
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,610
it was once a living,

129
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:45,690
breathing person—

130
00:06:46,159 --> 00:06:47,270
and so young.

131
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:57,560
Morning, Princess.

132
00:06:57,580 --> 00:06:59,040
Want to take a bath with me?

133
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:03,510
Oh my god!

134
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,310
I've unlocked the shared bath achievement

135
00:07:05,310 --> 00:07:06,640
with my husband Yuanji!

136
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,710
Let me see! Let me see!

137
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:09,950
You are amazing!

138
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:11,750
-You're amazing!
-You're incredible!

139
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:12,680
How did you do it?

140
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:13,960
How long did it take?

141
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,310
Is there some trick to it?

142
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:16,160
Come on, share it with us!

143
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,490
Yeah, I want to know too!

144
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:22,040
Wang Fang,

145
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,800
you're playing mobile games again.

146
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,650
Director,

147
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:27,200
I've finished writing
the scripts for today.

148
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,240
Generated by AI, huh?

149
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:31,240
I think they're pretty decent.

150
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:31,770
Xiaoni,

151
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,000
how are the numbers looking lately?

152
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:35,240
None of the seven influencers our team

153
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,870
is responsible for are performing well.

154
00:07:36,870 --> 00:07:38,830
The performance metrics
have remained flat.

155
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:40,190
Stop spending all your time
on in-game romances

156
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:41,750
and come up with some real ideas.

157
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:43,280
They'd have to listen first.

158
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,140
I spend forever

159
00:07:44,159 --> 00:07:45,190
planning skits for them,

160
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:45,920
and then they say

161
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:48,060
they're too tacky or bad for their image.

162
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:48,800
They all think they can just stand there,

163
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,360
do a bit of dancing,
and go viral overnight.

164
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:51,040
As if

165
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:52,430
the platform were short on pretty girls.

166
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:53,950
They all crank up the beauty filters,

167
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:55,600
and in real life,
they don't even look as good as me.

168
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,930
Why don't you become a streamer yourself?

169
00:07:57,950 --> 00:07:59,750
I think that's actually viable.

170
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:01,690
The content has become too homogeneous.

171
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:02,600
We have to highlight

172
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,870
what makes them stand out.

173
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:04,470
Director,

174
00:08:04,610 --> 00:08:05,310
the boss wants everyone

175
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:06,270
in the conference room

176
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:06,800
now.

177
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:14,730
"Clouds adorn her gown;
flowers mirror her beauty.

178
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:18,600
The spring breeze brushes the railing,
rich with fragrant dew.

179
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:21,530
Had one not beheld her
atop Jade Mountain's peak,

180
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:25,400
one would take her for a fairy
from the moonlit Jade Terrace."

181
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:26,510
Yan Yuzhen?

182
00:08:27,630 --> 00:08:28,480
Smart move.

183
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,950
Riding on Yan Yuzhen's popularity.

184
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:33,480
Looks like
she's had a bit of plastic surgery.

185
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,510
I... will be back.

186
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,400
She's really beautiful.

187
00:08:39,549 --> 00:08:41,270
The filter isn't even that heavy.

188
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,440
There are some traces of plastic surgery,

189
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,960
but nothing excessive.

190
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:45,810
My goodness,

191
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:47,550
2.73 million likes!

192
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:49,790
And it's still climbing!

193
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,520
It's 2.9 million now!

194
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,460
And this is her only video.

195
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:57,110
Posted just three hours ago.

196
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:59,320
Videos like this are common,

197
00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:01,150
but for one to blow up this fast?

198
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:03,210
She is pretty and has luck on her side,

199
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,900
so the traffic just comes.

200
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,770
Does she have an agency yet?

201
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:09,290
We're the best

202
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,520
MCN agency around.

203
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,570
And you're my best director.

204
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,870
I leave this woman to you.

205
00:09:13,870 --> 00:09:15,270
You must sign her.

206
00:09:15,530 --> 00:09:16,200
Check her background

207
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,660
to see if there's any dirt.

208
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,790
A hero's origins don't matter—

209
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:21,170
let alone an influencer's.

210
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:22,270
Her username is perfect.

211
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,400
No need to change it.

212
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,520
We'll reach out to her immediately.

213
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:25,030
Move fast.

214
00:09:25,030 --> 00:09:26,510
I must get this woman.

215
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:27,510
Copy that.

216
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:31,470
Director,

217
00:09:32,470 --> 00:09:33,510
Yan Yuzhen requested

218
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:34,840
to speak with you directly.

219
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,150
She wants your phone number.

220
00:09:36,150 --> 00:09:36,950
Give it to her.

221
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:45,320
Hello?

222
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,060
Are you Yan Yuzhen?

223
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,240
Hello, Director.

224
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:54,680
I'd like to meet you.

225
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,030
Meet me?

226
00:09:56,390 --> 00:09:57,590
I've checked around.

227
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,330
You are indeed

228
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,020
the best MCN agency right now,

229
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:03,210
and you are the best director.

230
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,000
I'm willing to give you this chance.

231
00:10:06,390 --> 00:10:07,720
Thank you for your trust.

232
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,580
Do you have time

233
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,800
to come in and chat at our office?

234
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,220
Actually, would it be convenient

235
00:10:13,390 --> 00:10:15,120
for you to come meet me instead?

236
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:15,870
Sure.

237
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:17,870
Just name the time and place.

238
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:19,280
How about

239
00:10:19,510 --> 00:10:20,910
your coffee shop?

240
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,670
Convenience Store 444.

241
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,240
Tonight.

242
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,200
How did you know?

243
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:34,200
Yuanji.

244
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,760
I've soaked for too long,

245
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,730
and I have no strength left.

246
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:54,900
"The maid helped her up,
languid and delicate."

247
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:08,870
Hello. It's you.

248
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:11,280
Is your boss around?

249
00:11:11,970 --> 00:11:12,970
Our boss went out.

250
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,360
I'll have an Americano, iced.

251
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:15,690
Sure.

252
00:11:21,790 --> 00:11:22,790
Basketball boys!

253
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,500
Want some iced coffee?

254
00:11:25,910 --> 00:11:26,550
My treat.

255
00:11:34,670 --> 00:11:35,320
Dapeng.

256
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,490
Your name is Dapeng, right?

257
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,320
You like basketball?

258
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,080
Are you good at it?

259
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:45,490
I used to play all the time.

260
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,200
After starting high school,

261
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,580
I barely played at all.

262
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:50,910
Why?

263
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:52,860
My mom wouldn't let me.

264
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:55,410
She said it'd distract me from my studies.

265
00:11:57,030 --> 00:11:57,750
Do you play?

266
00:11:58,510 --> 00:11:59,790
Not really. I'm no good at it.

267
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:01,650
I like watching the games though.

268
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:03,270
You must know Jordan, right?

269
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:04,670
Who doesn't know Jordan?

270
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:06,260
The guy who liked to chew gum

271
00:12:06,260 --> 00:12:07,120
and stick out his tongue

272
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:07,980
when he played—

273
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,340
the God of Basketball.

274
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:10,740
I can do all his layups.

275
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:13,810
I play really well.

276
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:14,700
My buddies

277
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:16,230
even call me Little Jordan.

278
00:12:17,630 --> 00:12:18,290
Sounds like

279
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:20,320
you really love basketball.

280
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,680
Do you still want to play now?

281
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:26,960
No.

282
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,410
Basketball won't get me anywhere.

283
00:12:32,110 --> 00:12:33,030
If only I were good

284
00:12:33,030 --> 00:12:33,760
at studying.

285
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,090
Then my mom would be very happy.

286
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,650
I have to go to tutoring.

287
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:44,270
You play so well.

288
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:46,360
Has your mom ever seen you play?

289
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:49,490
My mom hates it when I play basketball.

290
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:50,660
It doesn't matter.

291
00:12:51,150 --> 00:12:52,910
I just want my mom to be happy

292
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,220
and proud of me.

293
00:12:54,830 --> 00:12:55,410
That is

294
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:56,840
the most important thing to me—

295
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:58,570
more important than anything.

296
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:01,390
Sir!

297
00:13:01,790 --> 00:13:02,150
Sir!

298
00:13:02,510 --> 00:13:02,960
Could you please

299
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:04,620
throw the ball back over here?

300
00:13:05,670 --> 00:13:06,270
Thank you!

301
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:10,710
-Come on, let's keep playing!
-Come on!

302
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:11,960
Nice shot!

303
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,060
Hello, Granny.

304
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,120
Dapeng,

305
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,480
you really need to work harder.

306
00:13:26,870 --> 00:13:28,400
You're repeating the year.

307
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:30,120
Do you know how much

308
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:31,470
a year's tutoring costs?

309
00:13:31,470 --> 00:13:32,510
If you fail again,

310
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,640
Mom will be really heartbroken.

311
00:13:34,850 --> 00:13:35,450
Look at

312
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:37,270
your third great-uncle's child—

313
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:38,790
he got into a top-tier university
on his first try.

314
00:13:38,790 --> 00:13:39,750
You're not naturally bright,

315
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:41,550
so you have to work twice as hard!

316
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:42,630
I've pinned

317
00:13:42,870 --> 00:13:44,150
all my hopes on you.

318
00:13:45,030 --> 00:13:45,750
As long as you

319
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:47,480
can get into a good university,

320
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,000
every hardship and sacrifice I make

321
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:49,930
will be worth it.

322
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:32,410
Why did you come to this apartment?

323
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,930
Who are you looking for?

324
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,000
I...

325
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:37,600
I'm here to see the place that's for rent.

326
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,720
Young man,

327
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:40,870
you must not move in here.

328
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:41,870
Why not?

329
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,320
This place is haunted.

330
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:46,320
The mother was stewing chicken

331
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:47,390
over a small charcoal stove

332
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:50,650
in the room. The buildup of
carbon monoxide poisoned them,

333
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:53,430
and the smoke suffocated the son to death.

334
00:14:53,910 --> 00:14:54,630
Really?

335
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,360
I'm telling you—

336
00:14:56,630 --> 00:14:58,320
I can still hear it.

337
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:15,670
Zhao Hengzhi?

338
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,330
You're here.

339
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:21,680
You're here too?

340
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:26,770
I've found out everything.

341
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:30,140
Who are you people?

342
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:32,270
What are you doing in my home?

343
00:15:32,430 --> 00:15:34,030
We're here for your son.

344
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:37,050
He's not here anymore.

345
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,730
Who exactly are you?

346
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:41,200
I'm calling the police.

347
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:42,400
We're not bad people.

348
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:43,360
We came

349
00:15:43,390 --> 00:15:44,440
for Dapeng.

350
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:00,430
I was very tired that day.

351
00:16:04,190 --> 00:16:05,270
How could I have known

352
00:16:05,270 --> 00:16:08,070
that I'd fallen asleep
while stewing the chicken?

353
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:12,950
How could I have known

354
00:16:13,950 --> 00:16:15,790
the chicken soup would boil over

355
00:16:15,810 --> 00:16:16,940
and put out the fire?

356
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:23,320
He had no idea.

357
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:28,150
He was still studying

358
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:31,960
and just fell asleep right here.

359
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:36,960
I'm the worst mother in the world.

360
00:16:43,950 --> 00:16:45,050
I killed my son

361
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:46,550
with my own hands.

362
00:16:49,150 --> 00:16:50,960
What do I have left to live for?

363
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:53,600
Did you know?

364
00:16:55,790 --> 00:16:56,750
Even now,

365
00:16:57,390 --> 00:16:58,390
Dapeng is still working hard

366
00:16:58,390 --> 00:16:59,450
toward your dream.

367
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:05,960
Now?

368
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:10,030
My dream?

369
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:13,599
Do you know

370
00:17:13,619 --> 00:17:15,020
what Dapeng's dream was?

371
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:38,300
I've got a basketball game arranged.

372
00:17:38,310 --> 00:17:39,310
It's almost time.

373
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:49,270
Li,

374
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:50,750
I have an important guest.

375
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:51,880
Don't let anyone into the back room.

376
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:52,280
Got it.

377
00:17:58,590 --> 00:17:59,440
Welco...

378
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:00,880
Look.

379
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:02,750
He's so handsome.

380
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:05,440
My Queen,

381
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:06,680
this way, please.

